content:
Track Einstein Classification App Performance

The performance dashboard shows you how well Einstein’s predictions are working. View the performance of predictions compared to the field value at the time the case is closed.

Einstein Case Classification and Einstein Case Wrap-Up are available in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

User permissions needed:

View Setup
Customize Application
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
Edit on cases or Modify All Data

From Setup, enter Einstein Classification and select a model. On the Overview tab, select the field of interest and date range to display performance information for closed cases.

The dashboard shows the total number of closed cases with predicted field values, regardless of whether predictions were rejected, accepted, ignored, or automatically saved. Closed cases that didn’t receive recommendations aren’t counted.

Tableau for CRM customers can use the new Einstein Case Classification Value Dashboard managed package to quickly build and dig into reports and visualizations for classification’s business value, KPIs, and exclusive analytics.

Performance dashboards are just one way to monitor the impact of Einstein classification apps. Use platform events, custom reports, or key performance indicators (KPIs) to assess the impact of Einstein classification apps.

Available metrics include:

Average handle-time
Average time to resolve a case
Number of cases triaged per day, week, or month
Number of cases auto-triaged per day, week, or month
Number of reopened cases
Number of escalated cases
Case data completion
title: Einstein Classification App Performance Tracking
